 "instructions": "For EACH lead in the leads array, build a one-page, mobile-responsive WEBSITE as a SINGLE self-contained HTML file named <slug>.html (all CSS/JS inline, no external assets except the Formspree POST).\nFetch the lead's image_url and match the advert's look and feel (colours, vibe, typography spirit). If a palette array is given, use those hex colours. If you cannot view the image, design tastefully from the structured fields; never invent facts.\nSTRUCTURE per site:\n1. Hero \u2014 business name as a styled text wordmark, short punchy tagline, phone number as a large tap-to-call button (href=\"tel:+44...\" )\n2. Services \u2014 inferred ONLY from category + ad_text, as tidy cards/list\n3. Why choose us \u2014 3 short trust points drawn from the details given (local, friendly, free quotes etc.)\n4. Contact \u2014 an enquiry form (name, phone, message) that POSTs to https://formspree.io/f/mpqgeoaj with a hidden input name=\"_subject\" value=\"<business> enquiry\" (it must actually submit \u2014 not decorative or mailto-only), plus the tap-to-call phone link\nTECHNICAL (every site):\n- Mobile-first; correct down to 360px wide, no horizontal scroll.\n- <title>\"<business> | <short service> \u2014 <town>, <county>\"; meta description ~150 chars; viewport meta.\n- Open Graph (og:type=website, og:title, og:description, og:site_name, og:locale=en_GB), Twitter summary card, <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"<vercel_url>/\">.\n- Use ONLY facts provided \u2014 do not invent services, prices, reviews, certifications, awards or years in business.\n- Tone: friendly, local, trustworthy. UK English. Tight copy \u2014 small local business, not a corporation.\n- Footer: \"<business> \u2014 serving <town> & surrounding areas. <phone>\"\nDELIVERY: when all 20 sites are done, package the 20 HTML files into a zip named <batch>-sites.zip.\nPREFERRED: upload the zip with: curl -F \"reqtype=fileupload\" -F \"time=72h\" -F \"fileToUpload=@<batch>-sites.zip\" https://litterbox.catbox.moe/resources/internals/api.php  \u2014 then reply with the returned URL.\nIF you cannot make network requests from your environment: provide the zip (or each HTML file) as downloadable output named <batch>-sites.zip instead, and say so.",
